void.string: # This function must return an element or an array of elements. # elt the current element the node is executed on. # index the index of "elt" in the parent node return list. # maxIndex the last possible index in the parent node return list. # ctx the iteration context. def navigate(elt, index, maxIndex, ctx): messages = set() for communicationChannel in elt.getStarted(): messages |= set(communicationChannel.getEndToStartMessage()) for communicationChannel in elt.getEnded(): messages |= set(communicationChannel.getStartToEndMessage()) return messages

# This function is called when computing hyperlinks on this diagram. # It must return a valid element, or 'None'. # elt the element reprensented in the diagram. # diagram the diagram the element is unmasked in. def getMapping(self, elt, diagram): return elt
